00:00:27.658 --> 00:00:31.284
This is really what's the length
of segment A prime C prime?

00:00:31.284 --> 00:00:35.092
So they want the length
of this right over here.

00:00:35.092 --> 00:00:37.174
How do we figure that out?

00:00:37.174 --> 00:00:40.741
Well, the key realization
here is a reflection

00:00:40.741 --> 00:00:42.908
is a rigid transformation.

00:00:43.966 --> 00:00:48.049
Rigid transformation,
which is a very fancy word.

00:00:48.931 --> 00:00:51.227
But it's really just saying
that it's a transformation

00:00:51.227 --> 00:00:56.155
where the length between
corresponding points don't change.

00:00:56.155 --> 00:00:58.923
If we're talking about
a shape like a triangle,

00:00:58.923 --> 00:01:01.442
the angle measures won't change,

00:01:01.442 --> 00:01:05.015
the perimeter won't change,
and the area won't change.

00:01:05.015 --> 00:01:07.702
So we're gonna use the
fact that the length

00:01:07.702 --> 00:01:10.140
between corresponding points won't change.

00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:12.293
So the length between A prime and C prime

00:01:12.293 --> 00:01:16.274
is gonna be the same as
the length between A and C.

00:01:16.274 --> 00:01:20.527
So A prime C prime is
going to be equal to AC,

00:01:20.527 --> 00:01:23.030
which is equal to they
tell us right over there.

00:01:23.030 --> 00:01:25.443
That's this corresponding
side of the triangle.

00:01:25.443 --> 00:01:27.237
That has a length of three.

00:01:27.237 --> 00:01:28.696
So we answered the first question.

00:01:28.696 --> 00:01:30.027
